  "metadata": {
    "title": "CVE-2015-6855 Qemu: ide: divide by zero issue (low)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2015-6855",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2015-6855",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: It has been discovered that a QEMU emulator built with IDE disk and CD/DVD-ROM emulation support is vulnerable to a divide-by-zero issue. The flaw could occur when executing IDE's WIN_READ_NATIVE_MAX command to determine the maximum size of a drive. A privileged user inside the guest could use this flaw to crash the QEMU instance, resulting in a denial of service. \n            STATEMENT: This issue affects the versions of kvm and xen packages as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5.\n\nThis issue affects the versions of the qemu-kvm packages as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 and 7.\n\nThis issue affects the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 based versions of qemu-kvm-rhev packages as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization 3.\n\nThis issue affect the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7 based versions of the qemu-kvm-rhev packages as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization 3.",
